==English==
{{wikipedia}}

===Etymology===
From {{compound|en|iron|wood}}, because of its toughness.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# Any of a number of tree [[species]] known locally for having a particularly solid [[wood]], or the wood itself.
# {{lb|en|AU}} Any of various trees with particularly solid wood (especially {{taxlink|Acacia esthrophiolata|species}}, {{taxlink|Acacia excelsa|species}} or {{taxlink|Erythrophleum chlorostachys|species}}), or the wood itself.
#*'''1987''', {{w|Bruce Chatwin}}, ''The Songlines'', Vintage 1998, p. 139:
#*:Lydia and the boys lived in a shabby, prefabricated house of three rooms, which had been set down in the shade of an '''ironwood'''.
# {{taxlink|Cyrilla racemiflora|species|ver=220821}} 

